HMD Global has launched its new entry-level smartphone the Nokia 1 Plus at MWC 2019. Powered by the Android Go edition of Android 9.0, the Nokia 1 Plus offers users lightweight versions of apps and games, as well as newer Android features like Google Assistant Go. The Nokia 1 Plus offers users a 5.45-inch IPS display in a 18:9 aspect ratio, packaged in a polycarbonate frame that comes in various colours – such as red, blue, and black. The phone includes an 8MP rear camera with features such as an LED flash, optimised autofocus, and colour-adaptive noise reduction, as well as a 5MP front camera. The 1 Plus will come in both single and dual-SIM options, a 2,500mAh battery, and 8GB internal storage, said the company. Pricing will start at $99. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>